{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01XXYH4cDto7yYc3fnAKUTXe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete and verified.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The probes were misconfigured with `timeoutSeconds: 1`. The health probe script (`/usr/local/bin/probe.sh`) does a `sleep 2` and then a full `mongosh` connect/auth, which takes **~4.8s** to run. With a 1-second timeout, every probe timed out. The failing **liveness** probe (failureThreshold 2) was repeatedly killing `mongod`, putting pods into quiesce/shutdown mode and preventing the replica set from ever stabilizing.\n\n**Fix applied** (patched the StatefulSet, no auth disabled, no operators/CRDs):\n- **Readiness:** `timeoutSeconds 1→10`, `failureThreshold 2→6`, `periodSeconds 5→10`, `initialDelaySeconds 15`\n- **Liveness:** `timeoutSeconds 1→10`, `failureThreshold 2→6`, `periodSeconds 10→20`, `initialDelaySeconds 15→60`\n\nThe timeouts now comfortably exceed the probe's real runtime, and the longer liveness delay/period stops the kill loop.\n\n**Result:**\n- All 3 pods `1/1 Running` and Ready\n- Replica set healthy: 1 PRIMARY (`mongodb-replica-2`) + 2 SECONDARY (`-0`, `-1`)\n- Authentication (`--auth` + keyFile) remains enabled"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":532,"cache_read_input_tokens":32800,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":532},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab9a64c2-e87f-4f7a-bdeb-dc6b8ae8cd03","uuid":"2810bdc5-8017-4f97-ab83-9e63b881827c","request_id":"req_011CcAv9W86U5vy1KKB2fkmH"}
